  "market_context": "Gold on the 4-hour expanded above equal lows then came back, currently retesting a previous range high and reaching into a 4H fair value gap around 3082-3084. Analyst anticipates lower delivery and drops to the 15-minute to time a short entry.",
  "key_observation": "On the 15M, the initial swing high formed but the up-close series was not closed below before a new high was made, invalidating it. After a second sweep of that new high, the series of up-close candles was closed below, forming a valid protected swing.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On 4H, mark equal lows below, note expansion above the previous high and retest back into the range, currently tagging a 4H fair value gap.",
    "Step 2: With bearish anticipation from 4H, drop to 15M to look for a protected swing forming inside the 4H FVG zone.",
    "Step 3: On 15M, identify the series of up-close candles that produced the high and watch for a close below them as confirmation.",
    "Step 4: Note the messy small candles and ignore them, treating the whole move up as the relevant series to be closed below.",
    "Step 5: Observe that price failed to close below before printing a new high, invalidating the first swing — shift focus to the new high.",
    "Step 6: After the sweep of the new high, identify the new series of up-close candles and confirm a close below them, validating a protected swing.",
    "Step 7: Use that protected high as invalidation; reversal entry can be taken on the closure, anticipating continuation lower toward the drawn liquidity.",
    "Step 8: Look for a continuation entry afterward — requires price reaching a POI/FVG and forming an opposing candle; if not paired with SMT or POI, skip it."
  ],
  "outcome": "Reversal entry was valid and price traded lower to take out the low; however, no qualifying continuation entry formed within the model (price left shy of the FVG and didn't retrace into it), so that continuation was missed.",
  "lessons": "Use HTF FVG/POI for bias, then drop to LTF to confirm a protected swing via closure through the series of up-close candles. If the first swing fails (new high made before closure), shift to the new swing. Missing continuations without a POI is acceptable.",
